<topic id="dita-ot-transformation">
  <title>DITA-OT Transformation</title>
  <shortdesc>This type of transformation specifies the parameters for an Ant transformation that
    executes a DITA-OT build script. <ph keyref="product"/> includes a built-in version of Ant and a
    built-in version of DITA-OT, but other versions can be set in the scenario.</shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Transformation Scenarios<indexterm>DITA-OT</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>DITA-OT transformation scenario</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p id="p1">To create a <uicontrol>DITA-OT Transformation</uicontrol> scenario, use one of the
      following methods:<ul id="ul_ot1_lnt_1r">
        <li id="li_kql_cgk_54b" irina="irina">Use the <uicontrol><image href="../img/TransformConfig16.png" id="image_odd_1wv_sr"
            />Configure Transformation Scenario(s) (<shortcut
              conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_shift_c_shortcut"
              product="author developer editor"/><shortcut
              conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/alt_shift_tc_shortcut"
              product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"/>)</uicontrol> action from the
            <uicontrol>DITA Maps Manager</uicontrol> toolbar, main toolbar, or the <menucascade
            product="author developer editor">
            <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Transformation</uicontrol>
          </menucascade><uicontrol product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"
            >XML</uicontrol> menu. Then click the <uicontrol>New</uicontrol> button and select
            <uicontrol>DITA-OT Transformation</uicontrol>.</li>
        <li id="li_lql_cgk_54b" irina="irina">Go to <menucascade>
            <uicontrol>Window</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Show View</uicontrol>
          </menucascade> and select <uicontrol><image href="../img/TransformConfig16.png"
              id="image_dth_1wv_sr"/>Transformation Scenarios</uicontrol> to display <xref
            href="scenarios-view.dita#scenarios-view">this view</xref>. Click the <uicontrol><image
              href="../img/NewScenarioDrop.png"/>New Scenario</uicontrol> drop-down menu button and
          select <uicontrol>DITA-OT Transformation</uicontrol>.</li>
      </ul></p>
    <p id="p_mql_cgk_54b">Both methods open the <uicontrol>DITA Transformation Type</uicontrol> dialog box that
      presents the list of possible outputs. </p>
    <p id="p_nql_cgk_54b">
      <fig id="fig_lvk_mzt_rp" product="author developer editor">
        <title>DITA Transformation Type Dialog Box</title>
        <image href="../img/sa_select_dita_transform_dialog.png" id="image_nwk_mzt_rp"
          placement="inline"/>
      </fig>
    </p>
    <p id="p_oql_cgk_54b">
      <fig id="fig_amy_n4t_1r" product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">
        <title>DITA Transformation Type Dialog Box</title>
        <image href="../img/ec_select_dita_transform_dialog.png" id="image_pny_n4t_1r"
          placement="inline"/>
      </fig>
    </p>
    <p id="p_pql_cgk_54b">Select the desired type of output and click <uicontrol>OK</uicontrol>. This opens the
        <uicontrol>New Scenario</uicontrol> dialog box.</p>
    <p conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/name-storage-options"
      product="author developer editor" id="p_qql_cgk_54b"/>
    <p product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse" id="p_rql_cgk_54b">The upper part of the dialog box
      allows you to specify the <uicontrol>Name</uicontrol> of the transformation scenario.</p>
    <p id="p_sql_cgk_54b">The lower part of the dialog box contains several tabs that allow you to configure the
      options that control the transformation.</p>
  </body>
</topic>
